WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:27.800
What's the schedule today?

00:27.800 --> 00:30.800
I'm going to talk to you about the new Twin Baby Dolls.

00:30.800 --> 00:31.800
Okay.

00:31.800 --> 00:34.800
Telephone Mrs. Asciy at the advertising agency.

00:34.800 --> 00:36.800
I did that. Go on.

00:36.800 --> 00:38.800
11 o'clock approved the sketches for the toy spaceship.

00:38.800 --> 00:39.800
Where are they?

00:39.800 --> 00:40.800
Right here.

00:40.800 --> 00:42.800
Did you look at them?

00:42.800 --> 00:44.800
Yes I did.

00:44.800 --> 00:46.800
What do you think of the spaceship?

00:46.800 --> 00:48.800
I think the kids love it.

00:48.800 --> 00:51.800
Would you show me the drawings please?

00:51.800 --> 00:56.800
Huh.

00:56.800 --> 01:03.800
Now what else is on the schedule today?

01:03.800 --> 01:07.800
Well at one o'clock you have a lunch appointment with Mr. Levine,

01:07.800 --> 01:09.800
the client from the Toytown stores?

01:09.800 --> 01:10.800
Where?

01:10.800 --> 01:11.800
At Rosano's.

01:11.800 --> 01:14.800
Anything else?

01:14.800 --> 01:17.800
At four o'clock you have a meeting with the production staff in the conference room?

01:17.800 --> 01:20.800
Make sure everybody is at that meeting.

01:20.800 --> 01:21.800
We'll do.

01:21.800 --> 01:24.800
At six year meeting Mr. Rosawa.

01:24.800 --> 01:27.800
Oh yes. Are his models here?

01:27.800 --> 01:28.800
They're in my office.

01:28.800 --> 01:29.800
I'd like to see them.

01:29.800 --> 01:30.800
Right.

01:30.800 --> 01:32.800
What else?

01:36.800 --> 01:38.800
Come on Sam.

01:38.800 --> 01:41.800
You worked too hard Susan.

01:41.800 --> 01:44.800
When was your last day off?

01:44.800 --> 01:46.800
Hmm. I can't remember.

01:46.800 --> 01:49.800
You really ought to take some time off.

01:49.800 --> 01:50.800
What for?

01:50.800 --> 01:53.800
To enjoy the simple things in life.

01:53.800 --> 01:55.800
I know Sam.

01:55.800 --> 01:57.800
Maybe soon.

01:57.800 --> 02:00.800
To smell the flowers.

02:00.800 --> 02:01.800
Wait a minute.

02:01.800 --> 02:03.800
What's today's date?

02:03.800 --> 02:05.800
Today is the 12th one.

02:05.800 --> 02:09.800
It seems to me I scheduled something else.

02:13.800 --> 02:16.800
There's nothing else in the appointment book.

02:16.800 --> 02:18.800
I'm sure I did.

02:18.800 --> 02:21.800
Oh well. I'll probably remember it later.

02:22.800 --> 02:24.800
I hope it isn't important.

02:24.800 --> 02:26.800
It's probably nothing.

02:26.800 --> 02:28.800
Okay let's get started.

02:28.800 --> 02:31.800
Would you call Priscilla Smith at FAO Shorts please?

02:31.800 --> 02:32.800
Right.

02:38.800 --> 02:41.800
These are the models from the Japanese filmmaker.

02:41.800 --> 02:44.800
Thank you. Just put them on my desk.

02:45.800 --> 02:50.800
And the new drawings for the toy spaceship.

02:50.800 --> 02:52.800
Wonderful.

03:00.800 --> 03:02.800
That was fast.

03:02.800 --> 03:04.800
We have a new artist. She's very talented.

03:04.800 --> 03:07.800
And what time is it anyway my watch start?

03:07.800 --> 03:09.800
It's 1130.

03:09.800 --> 03:12.800
What time is my lunch date with Bill Levine?

03:12.800 --> 03:14.800
One o'clock.

03:14.800 --> 03:17.800
Remind me to leave at 1245.

03:17.800 --> 03:20.800
Did you remember your other appointment for today?

03:20.800 --> 03:22.800
No.

03:22.800 --> 03:26.800
But I have a feeling it's going to be too late when I do remember.

03:38.800 --> 03:40.800
Yes Sam?

03:40.800 --> 03:43.800
I just saw a mystery.

03:43.800 --> 03:44.800
What did I forget?

03:44.800 --> 03:47.800
You have some guests in the reception room.

03:47.800 --> 03:49.800
What? Who?

03:49.800 --> 03:52.800
Mr. Bennett and his daughter?

03:52.800 --> 03:54.800
I remember.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.800
Oh Harry.

03:56.800 --> 04:00.800
I made a lunch date with him and his daughter weeks ago.

04:00.800 --> 04:04.800
Is he a client?

04:04.800 --> 04:07.800
He's a friend.

04:07.800 --> 04:10.800
Well he's here with his daughter to have lunch.

04:10.800 --> 04:16.800
I met her at Thanksgiving and I promised to have lunch with both of them today.

04:16.800 --> 04:18.800
Yes indeed.

04:18.800 --> 04:22.800
What are you going to do about your appointment with Mr. Levine?

04:22.800 --> 04:25.800
Any suggestions?

